SIMPLE: prong
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prong
<hw>Prong</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>prangen</ets> to pinch, press, LG. <ets>prange</ets> a stick, or W.
<ets>procio</ets> to thrust, E. <ets>prowl</ets>,
<ets>pang</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A sharp-pointed instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prick it on a <qex>prong</qex> of iron.</q>
<rj><qau>Sandys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The tine of a fork, or of a similar instrument;
<as>as, a fork of two or three <ex>prongs</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A sharp projection,
as of an antler.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The fang of a tooth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prongbuck</ent>⟦br⟧
